==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Morning-glory
<hw>Morn"ing-glo`ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A climbing plant (<spn>Ipomoea purpurea</spn>) having handsome,
funnel-shaped flowers, usually red, pink, purple, white, or variegated,
sometimes pale blue. See <er>Dextrorsal</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Morningtide</ent>⟦br⟧
